			<div id="unique-entry-id-447" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Signed Copies</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 27 June 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-tour.php">Tour</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Immortal War" src="files/ImmortalWar.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></div>Just to clarify &ldquo;All school events this week but the bookshops I'm working with should have signed copies of IMWA.&rdquo;<br />Don&rsquo;t forget there is also a list of book shops selling signed copies at <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/SIGNEDCOPIESOFVAMPIRATESIMMORTALWAR/" rel="self">http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/</a><br />Thank you Captain.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-446" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Immortal War Schools Tour</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 27 June 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-tour.php">Tour</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="files/vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>The Immortal War Schools Tour is only visiting schools at the moment.  I am waiting for the summer holidays to hear if there will be any more.  The lucky schools are:&nbsp;<br />Monday&nbsp;27&nbsp;June 2011 - Bow School for Boys Event, Bow, London, UK and Stoke Newington School Event, Stoke Newington, London, UK<br />Tuesday&nbsp;28&nbsp;June 2011 - Trinity St. Peters Event, Formby, Merseyside, UK and Oldham Library and Lifelong Learning Centre Event, Oldham, Greater Manchester, UK (School event only)<br />Wednesday 29 June 2011 - St. Bede's Catholic High School Event, Lytham, Lancashire, UK and Lancaster Grammar Boys School Event&nbsp;, Lancaster, Lancashire, UK<br />Thursday&nbsp;30 June 2011 - Stonyhurst College Event, Clitheroe, Lancashire, UK and Clitheroe Royal Grammar School Event, Clitheroe, Lancashire, UK<br />Friday&nbsp;1 July 2011 - Hulme Hall School Event, Cheadle, Cheshire, UK and Hursthead Junior&nbsp;School Event , Cheadle, Cheshire, UK<br /><br />@JustinSomper wrote on Twitter<br />&ldquo;Day One of the Immortal War tour. Great morning with Victoria Park Books. Now early for train at Euston so a great Nando's opportunity!&rdquo;<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-444" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Immortal War Review</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 26 June 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="files/mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>I know many of you outside the UK are frustrated that you have to wait from six months to get your copies of the latest and last in the Vampirates series.  I just want to reassure you of the following:<br />1.	The story comes to a natural end at the end of the book.  There are a couple of loose ends, but not the kind that keeps you up at night and nothing in life ever wraps up as neatly as everyone wishes.<br />2.	Moonshine finally grows up.  He takes part as a character, not as an upset, spoilt brat as he did at the beginning of the series.<br />3.	All the characters stay in character, they do not do anything that you have not seen glimpses of them do before.<br />4.	Lastly, I loved it.  By the end of the third chapter the two characters I was most worried about, I knew had made peace (and were together) after the events that happened at the end of Empire of Night.<br /><br />I do not believe I have the right to force my ideas on other people and so that is my review.  As written by an author on Twitter &ldquo;Never let anyone tell you what books are and aren't &ldquo;good for you&rdquo;. Read and think.&rdquo;  Loads of things in life other people have told me are terrible or brilliant and I have found the reverse.  So enjoy reading, do things expecting it to be a wonderful experience and make up your own mind.<br /><br />Don&rsquo;t forget the Captain has promised us Lorcan Furey&rsquo;s story will be written in Grace&rsquo;s book of crossing stories.  Which he is under contract to write after the series has finished.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-445" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Newsround Hotseat</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 22 June 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="files/vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>If you have a question for the Captain last week you could have either gone to the VIP section of <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="self">www.vampirates.co.uk/</a> or to Newsround website, as the Captain was in the Hotseat last Friday.  The results have just been published on their website, so please go and check out <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/newsid_9510000/newsid_9510200/9510212.stm" rel="self">news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-443" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Penny Smith Chats to Justin Somper</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 18 June 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Sq_Rackham.jpg" src="files/Sq_Rackham.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>Radio 2 Arts Show: Penny Smith sits In at chats to Justin Somper at 1:30 / 2:00 - <a href="http://bbc.in/jJXMNY" rel="self">http://bbc.in/jJXMNY</a><br />This should be available abroad and in the UK until 12:02AM Sat, 25 Jun 2011 according to the website.<br /></div></div>
